<p class="">    <h1>Key Challenges in the Nylon 6 & 66 Market</h1>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Raw Material Price Volatility:</strong> The pricing of key raw materials such as caprolactam for Nylon 6 and hexamethylenediamine for Nylon 66 is highly susceptible to fluctuations in the petrochemical market, which can lead to unstable production costs.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Environmental Regulations:</strong> Stricter environmental regulations regarding emissions and waste management are making manufacturing processes more complex and expensive. Compliance with these regulations can hinder production efficiency and increase operational costs.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Competition from Alternative Materials:</strong> The growing adoption of bio-based and recycled materials poses a significant challenge to traditional Nylon 6 and 66 products. Industries seeking to improve sustainability are increasingly opting for alternatives, thereby threatening market share.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Technological Limitations:</strong> Current production technologies can be energy-intensive and require significant capital investment. Companies may find it challenging to innovate or upgrade their capabilities while dealing with cost constraints.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Supply Chain Disruptions:</strong> The COVID-19 pandemic and geopolitical uncertainties have highlighted vulnerabilities in the supply chain, leading to delays and increased costs for procurement, manufacturing, and distribution.        </li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Infrastructure Investment:</strong> Increased infrastructure development projects, particularly in automotive and construction sectors, are driving demand for high-performance Nylon 6 and 66 due to their durability and resistance to wear.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Technological Innovations: